2011-07-17  rocky  <rocky@gnu.org>

	There seems to be a bug in GNU make in showing target indentation when --trace or --debug=basic is on. This was noticed by reviewer B for LISA'11. I am not 100% certain of this fix since this is a little more aggressive than some smaller incremental changes. Also, I've change indentation to the more conventional two spaces rather than one for each level.

