	it has commands that do, use those to derive the target location.

2004-06-24  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	When printing location, If the target is an absolute filename, don't prepend starting-directory.  starting-directory is only needed if a relative filename.

	When printing target. If we don't have location info for the target
	but do have location info for the commands it runs, use that to derive
	a target location. (Right now we assume the target is the line before
	the line that the commands start.)

2004-06-24  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Cover the debugger's prior bugs.

2004-06-24  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Supply "-f Makefile" as default arguments. Previous commit was erroneous.

2004-06-18  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Add ability to selectively print information about a target.

2004-06-17  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	History numbering has been fixed up.

2004-06-17  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Small Doxyginization.

2004-06-17  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Remove private header definitions - use the public versions.

2004-06-17  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Make set_file_variables public. It's used by the debugger to make sure target commands get written out correctly.

2004-06-17  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Add remote-stub.h

2004-06-17  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Get local variables are set correctly in "write" command.

	Increase common code (decrease length) via a get_word routine.

2004-06-17  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Modernize prototypes and add header file.

2004-06-16  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Need to have -f Makefile in args.

2004-06-15  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Allow setting/showing more of the flags that can be set by make, i.e. ignnore-errors, keep-going, silent.

	Hack in fix for duplicate 0 history entry.

	Allow $@ as target name in "write" command.

	Add internationalization for many strings.

	com_...() -> dbg_cmd_..() to match bash debugger. Hey, why not?

2004-06-15  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Add doxygen comment on prototype

2004-06-14  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Do a tad better on expanding commands. In particular we remove leading \t and command prefix @, +, or -.

2004-06-13  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Add "write [target | [file]] to save commands to a file.  print will now use the default target as the thing to print if no variable or target is supplied.

	Note all of this in doc.

2004-06-13  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Update for new "write" command and changed "set" command.

2004-06-13  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Now is 0.2cvs

2004-06-13  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Expand the way set works. "set *var* *val*" is now "set variable *var* *val*" so we can accomodate

	set basename {on|off|toggle|
	set trace {on|off|toggle}

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Wrong readline variable set.

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Revise.

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	*** empty log message ***

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	ENABLE_READLINE -> HAVE_READLINE

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	It's now HAVE_READLINE instead of ENABLE_READLINE

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	there is probably a better way

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Replace bcmp, bzero and bcopy with memcmp, memset and memmove. Readline can't tollerate the make.h macros for these.

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	glob.c: remove K&R style prototype

	Makefile.in .deps/*: these shouldn't have gotten in CVS.

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Make debugger/general test now.

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Skip regression test for debugger if we don't have debug support.

	README: note we skip .cvsignore and xxx.in

2004-06-12  R. Bernstein  <rocky@gnu.org>

	Give a warning if debugger options were specified but we don't have debugger support compiled in.

